result.execSummary:
The defendant Kaia Mueller was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Robbery of a Financial Institution [Modifiers: Repeater], a class C felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.87.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Transcript of partial proceedings of Sentencing hearing before the Hon. David M. Reddy on June 2, 2016
Court Reporter:  Sandra Elderbrook
Temporary Commitment form filed
BOND QUASHED

9:01 am  Court in session.  Case called.  Appearances given.  
Haley Jo Johnson appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
Defendant Kaia  Mueller in court with attorney Travis Schwantes.  
Matter is before the Court for sentencing.  Court has reviewed the PSI as well as the other information that was provided by the Defense.  Attorney Schwantes has reviewed the PSI with Mr. Mueller and has one minor  correction.  
9:04 am  Atty Johnson makes record with regard to victim notification.  Court notes there is a Restitution request for $3,763.00.  
9:04 am  Argument as to sentence by Attorney Johnson.  
9:07 am  Court wants to resolve / clarify issue in the PSI wtith reference to defendant's prior sentence.  Response by Attorneys.  
9:07 am  Continued argument as to sentence by Attorney Johnson.  
9:11 am  Argument as to sentence by Attorney Schwantes.  
9:26 am  Statement by Seth Kirkpatrick on behalf of the defendant.  
9:30 am  Statement by Lauren Mueller on behalf of the defendant.  
9:34 am  Statement by the defendant.  
9:37 am  Court in recess.  Court will return at 10:00 am with its decision.  

10:00 am  Court in session.  Court proceeds with making its record and sentencing the Defendant.  
COURT SENTENCES DEFENDANT TO:

Eight (8) years in prison bifurcated into: 
Four (4) years of IC followed by four (4) years of ES
Sixty-eight (68) days of sentence credit 

CONDITIONS OF ES:
1)  Submit DNA sample and pay surcharge.  
2)  Obtain AODA assessment within 30 days of release from prison.  
3)  Obtain employment within 30 days of release from prison.  
4)  Pay all court obligations at least 90 days prior to discharge.  
5)  Pay supervision fees in a timely manner.  
6)  No contact with Fort Community Credit Union or with Marai Binagi.  
7)  No casinos.  
8)  No weapons  
9)  No alcohol.  No drugs or drug paraphernalia.  
9)  Pay restitution in the amount of $3,763.00.  

10:07 am  Court in recess.
